line_1: Which in its very Constitution lurk,
line_2: Too sure at last, to do its destin'd work;

line_1: Who slily did like snarling Blood-hound lurk,
line_2: Lent th' golden Mattock to this pious work,

line_1: Who slily did like snarling Blood-hound lurk,
line_2: And balk'd both Pagan, and the Christian Turk,

line_1: No idle wit, no trifling verse can lurk
line_2: In the deep bosom of that weighty work;

line_1: And embryo law-suits in a whisper lurk;
line_2: Where balls for advocates prepare their work,
